  "title": "Marketing Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Title:</strong> Marketing Executive – Mr Bucket</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br /><br />·       Develop and execute integrated marketing campaigns to drive brand awareness, customer acquisition, and revenue growth.</p><p>·       Lead the creation of marketing collaterals, including campaign assets, promotional materials, and digital content.</p><p>·       Analyse market trends, customer insights, and competitor activities to identify opportunities and propose strategic marketing actions.</p><p>·       Manage end-to-end campaign timelines, including procuring marketing collaterals, coordinating with internal teams, and tracking performance.</p><p>·       Oversee brand consistency across all communication touchpoints, ensuring alignment with brand guidelines.</p><p>·       Evaluate campaign performance using data and analytics, and present findings with actionable recommendations.</p><p>·       Assist in planning and executing VM, partnerships and Public Relations.</p><p>·       Work closely with cross functional departments to ensure smooth implementation of marketing promotions.</p><p>·       Manage marketing budgets and ensure efficient use of resources.<br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Marketing, Business, Communications, or related fields.</p></li><li><p>1–2 years of marketing experience, preferably in F&B, retail, hospitality, or consumer brands.</p></li><li><p>Strong communication, project management, and stakeholder management skills.</p></li><li><p>Creative, resourceful, and able to work independently in a fast-paced environment.</p></li><li><p>Proficiency in design tools such as Canva, Adobe Creative Suite, or Shopify is a plus<br /><br /></p></li></ul>",
